<title>Summary of Pharmacologic Differences
among Six Tricyclic Antidepressants
</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<h2>Table 4. Summary of Pharmacologic Differences<br>
among Six Tricyclic Antidepressants</h2>
<pre>
_______________________________________________________________________

<b>                          Anticholinergic       Block of Amine Pump	
Drug	          Sedation      Effects       Serotonin    Norepinephrine</b>
Imipramine         ++           ++              ++             ++
Amitriptyline      +++          +++             +++            +
Desipramine        +            +               0              +++
Nortriptyline      ++           ++              +              ++
Doxepin            +++          +++                    Weak
Protriptyline       0	        ++                   Not known
_______________________________________________________________________
</pre>
<p>0 = none;   + = slight;   ++ = moderate;   +++ = high
<p>Adapted from Holister LE: <b>Drug therapy: Tricyclic antidepressants</b>,<i> N Engl J Med 
</i>229:1106-1109,  1168-1171, 1978 and with permission in Weinberg WA, Emslie GJ: <b>Attention 
deficit hyperactivity disorder: The differential diagnosis</b>.<i> J Child Neurol 6(Suppl)</i>:S23-
S36, 1991. 

