<title>Prominent Causes Of Attention Deficit Hyperactivity Disorder 
</title>
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<h3 align=center> Table 6. Prominent Causes Of Attention Deficit 
Hyperactivity Disorder </h3>

<blockquote>
<dl>
<dt>DEVELOPMENTAL HYPERACTIVITY
<p>
<dt>AFFECTIVE ILLNESS (BIPOLAR DISORDER)
<dd>Dysthymia
<dd>Hypomania
<dd>Cyclothymia
<dd>Depression
<dd>Mania
<dd>Classic manic-depressive disease
<dd>Juvenile rapid cycling bipolar disease
<p>
<dt>PRIMARY DISORDER OF VIGILANCE
<p>
<dt>LEARNING DISABILITIES (task dependent)
<p>
<dt>NARCOLEPSY
<p>
<dt>PRIMARY CONDUCT DISORDER
<p>
<dt>CLASSIC FOCAL NEUROLOGICAL DEFICIT
<dd>Neglect
<dd>Inattention
</dl>
</blockquote>
