<A NAME="OSW"><H2>Other Relevant Software</H2>
<DL>

<DD><H3>TeX Materials</H3>
<UL>
<LI>
<!-- 
    <A HREF="http://jasper.ora.com/ctan.html">
    This site appears to be dead!
-->
    A HREF="http://sunsite.unc.edu/pub/packages/TeX/">
	Comprehensive Tex Archive Network</A>.  (
    <A HREF="http://www.SHSU.edu/cgi-bin/ctan-index">
	Search</A> the CTAN archive.)
    <BR>Also available at 
    <A HREF="http://www.shsu.edu:80/tex-archive/">
	Texan</A>, 
    <A HREF="http://www.tex.ac.uk/tex-archive/">
	British</A>, and 
    <A HREF="http://www.dante.de/dante/Ctan.html">
	German</A> sites.

<LI><A HREF="http://www.bluesky.com/">
	Blue Sky Research</A> makes a nice (commercial) version of TeX
	for the 
    <A HREF="http://www.info.apple.com/">
	Macintosh</A>.  (Other neat links on their page as well.)

<LI><A HREF="http://www.mathtype.com/mathtype/">
	MathType</A>.  A souped-up version of the Equation Editor found
	in Microsoft Word and several other word processors.  Will 
	translate its WYSIWYG equations into TeX format 
	(for both the Macintosh and some versions of Windows).

</UL>

<DD><H3>Mathematica</H3>
